    <div class="allianceSection collapsable collapsed">
        <h4 class="header">Regional Status</h4>
        
            <p>The range of <i>Vaccinium cespitosum</i> includes the Klamath Mountains (M261A), Central California Coast (261B), Northern California Coast (263A), Northern California Coast Ranges (M261Ba), and Warner Mountains (M261Gf).</p>
        

        <ul class="text">
        
            <li><b>Sierra Nevada</b> (M261Eo, Eq). Keeler-Wolf et al. (2003b) described two associations, one in the <i>Carex filifolia</i> alliance and the other in the <i>Calamagrostis muiriana</i> alliance in the Yosemite National Park study. Potter (2005) placed stands with <i>Kalmia microphylla</i> in a <i>Vaccinium cespitosum</i> alliance. We currently place these associations here.</li>
        
            <li><b>Southern Cascades</b> (M261Df). Imper (1988b, see Cheng 2004) described stands with <i>K. microphylla, Phyllodoce empetriformis,</i> and a variety of herbs in the Red Butte-Red Fir Ridge RNA on Mount Shasta.</li>
        
        </ul>
    </div>


    
	
